## 1. Executive Summary

**SpecSync Agent** is a GitHub Action that acts as an autonomous architectural guardrail on every commit and pull request. It reads feature specifications from the repository's GitHub Wiki — owned exclusively by architects, product managers, and QA — and validates every code change against those specs before tests are written or a PR is cleared for review.

It exists because junior developers and AI coding tools (vibe coding) generate plausible-looking code that has no meaningful alignment with what was actually specified — wrong architecture, missing tests, feature creep, and zero coverage of acceptance criteria.

> **Core pitch:**
> "SpecSync Agent is the guardrail between vibe coding and production. It enforces architectural intent on every commit, generates tests from acceptance criteria automatically, and ensures junior developers can't ship code that contradicts the spec — without ever leaving GitHub."

### Who It's For

| Role | What They Get |
|------|--------------|
| **Architect** | Their spec is enforced on every commit. Wiki is their domain. Misalignment escalates to them. |
| **QA** | Acceptance criteria they wrote get converted to tests automatically on every aligned commit. |
| **Engineering Manager** | Junior developers and AI tools can't bypass the architecture or skip tests. |
| **Developer** | Clear, inline feedback on what's missing. Self-service fixes for unintentional misalignment. |

