## 3. System Architecture

### Three Core Components

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    GITHUB WIKI                              │
│            (repo.wiki.git — separate git repo)              │
│     Write access: Architect, PM, QA only                   │
│     Read access: Everyone including SpecSync bot            │
│     Contains: Feature specs, acceptance criteria,           │
│               integration maps, API contracts               │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       │ read on every run
                       │ write: Option B wiki PR only
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              SPECSYNC AGENT (GitHub Action)                 │
│                                                             │
│  1. Parse git diff (what changed)                          │
│  2. Fetch relevant Wiki spec pages via GitHub API          │
│  3. Call Claude API: diff + spec → alignment verdict       │
│  4. Map impact radius (unit + integration scope)           │
│  5. Generate tests OR produce analysis file                │
│  6. Commit output back to branch via GitHub API            │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       │ commits to branch
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    CODE REPOSITORY                          │
│     /tests/                  ← committed on alignment      │
│     /feature-alignment/      ← committed on misalignment   │
│       (feature branches only, deleted on merge)            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Access Control Model

```
WIKI (repo.wiki.git)
  ├── Architect        → read + write
  ├── Product Manager  → read + write
  ├── QA Lead          → read + write
  ├── Developer        → read only
  └── SpecSync Bot     → read always
                          write only for Option B wiki PRs
                          (requires architect/PM approval)

CODE REPO
  ├── Developer        → read + write (feature branches)
  ├── Architect        → read + write + merge to main
  └── SpecSync Bot     → write to feature branches only
                          (test files + analysis files)
                          cannot push to main/develop
```

