## 4. The Two Triggers

SpecSync is activated by two completely separate events.

### Trigger 1 — Code Commit or PR

Standard GitHub Actions event. Fires on every push to a feature branch and every PR open/update.

```yaml
on:
  push:
    branches-ignore: [main, develop]   # feature branches only
  pull_request:
    types: [opened, synchronize]
```

Nothing special here — this is how every GitHub Action works.

### Trigger 2 — Wiki Spec Update

This is the smart trigger. When an architect updates a spec page in the Wiki, all blocked PRs that were waiting on that spec get automatically re-evaluated.

GitHub Wiki is a separate Git repo (`repo.wiki.git`). It does not natively fire GitHub Actions. The solution is a three-part relay:

```
Architect edits Wiki page and saves
          ↓
wiki.git receives a commit
          ↓
Wiki webhook fires (configured in repo Settings → Webhooks)
POST to relay endpoint with push payload
          ↓
Relay function (Cloudflare Worker / AWS Lambda — ~20 lines)
Extracts: which spec page changed, new commit SHA
Calls GitHub API:
  POST /repos/{owner}/{repo}/dispatches
  {
    "event_type": "wiki-spec-updated",
    "client_payload": {
      "spec_page": "feature-auth",
      "wiki_sha": "abc123"
    }
  }
          ↓
repository_dispatch fires in CODE REPO's GitHub Action
          ↓
SpecSync wakes up with wiki-spec-updated context
Queries: which open PRs have a /feature-alignment/ file
         that references this spec page?
Re-runs alignment check on each affected PR
```

#### Why a Relay Function?

The wiki webhook fires a raw `push` event payload. The GitHub dispatch API requires a specific JSON format plus an auth token. The relay is the translation layer between them — it's a one-time setup, ~20 lines of code, and runs on Cloudflare Workers for free.

#### Relay Function (complete):

```javascript
// Cloudflare Worker — wiki-to-dispatch relay
export default {
  async fetch(request, env) {
    const payload = await request.json();

    // Extract changed wiki page from push payload
    const changedFiles = payload.commits
      ?.flatMap(c => [...c.added, ...c.modified]) ?? [];

    if (changedFiles.length === 0) return new Response('no pages changed');

    // Fire repository_dispatch on the code repo
    const response = await fetch(
      `https://api.github.com/repos/${env.REPO_OWNER}/${env.REPO_NAME}/dispatches`,
      {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          'Authorization': `token ${env.GITHUB_TOKEN}`,
          'Accept': 'application/vnd.github+json',
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          event_type: 'wiki-spec-updated',
          client_payload: {
            spec_pages: changedFiles,
            wiki_sha: payload.after,
            updated_by: payload.pusher?.name,
          }
        })
      }
    );

    return new Response(response.ok ? 'dispatched' : 'failed', {
      status: response.ok ? 200 : 500
    });
  }
};
```

