## 9. Technical Stack

### Component Map

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| **Trigger — code** | GitHub Actions `on: [push, pull_request]` |
| **Trigger — wiki** | Wiki webhook → Cloudflare Worker relay → `repository_dispatch` |
| **AI reasoning** | Claude API (`claude-sonnet-4`) — diff + wiki spec → verdict + tests |
| **Wiki reading** | GitHub REST API: `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/wiki/pages/{title}` |
| **Wiki PR (Option B)** | GitHub REST API: commit to `repo.wiki.git` branch → open PR |
| **Test output** | Committed to branch via GitHub REST API |
| **Analysis output** | Committed to `/feature-alignment/` via GitHub REST API |
| **PR check status** | GitHub Checks API — pass/fail status on the PR |
| **PR comments** | GitHub PR Review API — structured inline review |
| **Post-merge cleanup** | GitHub Action step on `pull_request: closed` event |
| **Bot identity** | GitHub App (own identity, own token, clear audit trail) |
| **Packaging** | Reusable GitHub Action published to GitHub Marketplace |

### GitHub Action Workflow File

```yaml
# .github/workflows/specsync.yml
name: SpecSync Agent

on:
  push:
    branches-ignore: [main, develop, staging]
  pull_request:
    types: [opened, synchronize, reopened]
  pull_request:
    types: [closed]        # for post-merge cleanup
  repository_dispatch:
    types: [wiki-spec-updated]   # fired by wiki relay

jobs:
  specsync:
    # Skip bot commits to prevent infinite loop
    if: "!contains(github.event.head_commit.message, '[specsync]')"
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    timeout-minutes: 10

    permissions:
      contents: write        # commit test + analysis files
      pull-requests: write   # post reviews, set check status

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
        with:
          fetch-depth: 2

      - name: Run SpecSync Agent
        uses: your-org/specsync-agent@v1
        with:
          anthropic-api-key: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}
          github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
          wiki-relay-secret: ${{ secrets.WIKI_RELAY_SECRET }}

  cleanup:
    if: github.event.pull_request.merged == true
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Remove feature-alignment folder
        run: |
          if [ -d "feature-alignment" ]; then
            git rm -rf feature-alignment/
            git commit -m "[specsync] cleanup: remove alignment analysis post-merge"
            git push
          fi
```

### Security Model

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — stored in GitHub Secrets, never in code or wiki
- `GITHUB_TOKEN` — auto-generated per run, scoped to the repo
- Wiki webhook uses HMAC-SHA256 signature verification — relay validates before dispatching
- Bot (GitHub App) operates with minimum required permissions
- Option B wiki changes go through PR review — bot cannot force-push to wiki main branch

