## 10. GitHub Action Delivery

### How It's Packaged

SpecSync Agent is distributed as a **composite GitHub Action** on the GitHub Marketplace. Any team adds it to their repo with one workflow file — no infrastructure to manage.

```yaml
# That's all a team needs to add to their repo:
- name: Run SpecSync Agent
  uses: specsync/specsync-agent@v1
  with:
    anthropic-api-key: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}
    github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
```

### Action Repository Structure

```
specsync-agent/                  ← the published action repo
  action.yml                     ← action metadata + inputs
  src/
    index.ts                     ← entry point
    diff-parser.ts               ← parse git diff
    wiki-reader.ts               ← fetch spec pages from wiki
    alignment-engine.ts          ← call Claude API
    impact-mapper.ts             ← dependency graph traversal
    test-generator.ts            ← generate and commit tests
    analysis-writer.ts           ← write misalignment analysis
    pr-reporter.ts               ← post GitHub PR review
    wiki-dispatch-handler.ts     ← handle wiki-spec-updated events
  relay/
    cloudflare-worker.js         ← wiki → dispatch relay (deploy once)
  docs/
    setup.md
    wiki-template.md             ← feature spec page template
    access-control.md
```

### Setup for a New Repo (5 steps)

1. Add `.github/workflows/specsync.yml` with the workflow file above
2. Add `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` to repo secrets
3. Deploy the Cloudflare Worker relay (one-time, per organisation)
4. Configure wiki webhook to point at the relay URL
5. Create Wiki pages for features using the spec template

